141
00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:36.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I also wanted to ask,
if you're busy later this evening...

142
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:38.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

143
00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:40.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, I'd like to take you
somewhere special

144
00:10:40.682 --> 00:10:43.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as a sign of appreciation
for all the hard work you do.

145
00:10:43.768 --> 00:10:45.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, uh... okay?

146
00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:48.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So...

147
00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:50.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is where
you're taking me?

148
00:10:50.525 --> 00:10:53.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're looking at a highly-concentrated
oxygen chamber

149
00:10:53.695 --> 00:10:55.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that Dr. Saito recently developed.

150
00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:59.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A prototype, anyway.
It's supposed to restore your health.

151
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:03.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I thought this would be a good chance
for the two of you to test it out.

152
00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:06.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The two of us?
Me and Doc Saito?

153
00:11:09.836 --> 00:11:11.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bunny! What are
you doin' here?

154
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was invited. Like you.

155
00:11:14.382 --> 00:11:16.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By... Mr. Maverick?

156
00:11:16.593 --> 00:11:21.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our young Barnaby has been exhausted
lately. He needed to take a break.

157
00:11:21.306 --> 00:11:26.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I apologize that you had to handle those
criminals without your partner today.

158
00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:29.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no problem.
Just another day at the office.

159
00:11:37.363 --> 00:11:40.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Saito] <i>So, how does it feel?</i>
<i>Your body seems lighter, doesn't it?</i>

160
00:11:41.034 --> 00:11:43.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Like you're drifting off</i>
<i>to a blissful sleep!</i>

161
00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:45.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just got in the damn tank.

162
00:11:46.039 --> 00:11:50.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Are you getting sleepy yet? Well?</i>
<i>How about now? Are you sound asleep?</i>

163
00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:51.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

164
00:11:51.628 --> 00:11:55.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Hey, Tiger! Are you in dream-land?</i>
<i>Is it relaxing? Tell me!</i>

165
00:11:55.924 --> 00:11:58.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't sleep
with you yelling!

166
00:11:59.344 --> 00:12:01.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Maverick] <i>Can you hear me, Barnaby?</i>

167
00:12:01.971 --> 00:12:04.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I understand how frustrated you must be.</i>

168
00:12:05.099 --> 00:12:07.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But if you give up now,</i>
<i>your goal will elude you.</i>

169
00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:09.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You won't have closure.</i>

170
00:12:10.021 --> 00:12:13.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sir, the trouble
I've caused... I'm sorry.

171
00:12:13.942 --> 00:12:17.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Just close your eyes and rest.</i>
<i>You'll get another chance soon enough.</i>

172
00:12:18.029 --> 00:12:19.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

173
00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:20.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Good night, Barnaby.</i>

174
00:12:23.409 --> 00:12:27.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[opera music plays]

175
00:12:47.308 --> 00:12:52.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

176
00:12:53.564 --> 00:12:55.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was so close.

177
00:12:55.942 --> 00:12:58.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[announcer] <i>Calling Tiger and</i>
<i>Barnaby! It's showtime!</i>

178
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:03.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Report immediately to the abandoned</i>
<i>church site located in the downtown area.</i>

179
00:13:03.157 --> 00:13:06.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I repeat, calling Tiger</i>
<i>and Barnaby. It's showtime!</i>

180
00:13:16.045 --> 00:13:17.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Been waiting long?

181
00:13:17.588 --> 00:13:20.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This time it's not a show,
we've got the real deal here.

182
00:13:20.967 --> 00:13:21.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I figured.

183
00:13:21.968 --> 00:13:24.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Apparently, the cops
are gonna raid the hideout

184
00:13:24.512 --> 00:13:26.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of some crime syndicate
they've been watching.

185
00:13:26.848 --> 00:13:28.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A crime syndicate?

186
00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:37.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're going live?
No tape delay?

187
00:13:37.358 --> 00:13:40.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It'll be a sensation.
Our ratings are gonna go through the roof!

188
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:43.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But ma'am, this is
supposed to be a surprise operation.

189
00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:46.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't airing it live
gonna tip off the criminals?

190
00:13:46.909 --> 00:13:49.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not if we get
really creative.

191
00:13:49.495 --> 00:13:50.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, let's
live a little.

192
00:13:52.957 --> 00:13:54.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-[Barnaby] Standby?</i>
<i>-[Tiger] Yep.</i>

193
00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:58.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>[Barnaby] Why is she making us wait?</i>
<i>The hideout is right down there!</i>

194
00:13:58.463 --> 00:14:01.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tiger] <i>The hell if I know. She just said</i>
<i>sit tight and wait for orders.</i>

195
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Justice Bureau gave
us approval.

196
00:14:09.932 --> 00:14:12.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've set up a direct</i>
<i>line of contact to the police.</i>

197
00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:15.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Once the heroes are in position,</i>
<i>they'll all move in on my command.</i>

198
00:14:16.064 --> 00:14:20.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>At that instant, you roll the cameras,</i>
<i>and </i>Hero TV <i>goes live!</i>

199
00:14:20.276 --> 00:14:23.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I get it. So they won't
have enough time to escape.

200
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:26.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I gotta admit,
the audience is gonna eat it up!

201
00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:29.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you getting excited?

202
00:14:29.535 --> 00:14:31.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[gulping]
No.

203
00:14:32.330 --> 00:14:34.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello Heroes!

204
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:41.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Agnes] <i>We know there are five</i>
<i>criminals holed up in that church.</i>

205
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:43.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They're heavily armed</i>
<i>and very dangerous.</i>

206
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:46.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>There may also be</i>
<i>NEXTs, so watch out!</i>

207
00:14:47.512 --> 00:14:50.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Just in case, the police</i>
<i>have set up roadblocks</i>

208
00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:52.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and sealed all entry</i>
<i>points around the area.</i>

209
00:14:53.684 --> 00:14:57.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen. The police have
spent months tracking down this syndicate.

210
00:14:57.814 --> 00:15:01.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You cannot let them get away.
<i>Hero TV's </i>reputation is at stake.

211
00:15:02.235 --> 00:15:03.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or... to put it another way...

212
00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:07.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Do a good job and</i>
<i>you'll rack up a huge amount of points.</i>

213
00:15:08.366 --> 00:15:10.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, you hear that?
I bet you're happy now.

214
00:15:12.703 --> 00:15:15.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, well I guess
points aren't everything.

215
00:15:15.790 --> 00:15:18.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tiger] You know, if those guys in
the hideout are from Ouroboros,

216
00:15:19.127 --> 00:15:21.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that NEXT with the blue flames
might make an appearance.

217
00:15:22.338 --> 00:15:26.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's been dropping criminals one by one.
Keepin' 'em quiet.

218
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:30.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Almost like he's cleanin' house
for his organization. Don't you think?

219
00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:34.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barnaby] Hm. I'm surprised you
figured that all out on your own.

220
00:15:34.434 --> 00:15:37.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Fire Emblem kinda
helped a little.

221
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:39.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course he did.

222
00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:44.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I get it, Bunny. I know how bad
you wanna go in and get your revenge.

223
00:15:44.694 --> 00:15:46.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But an order's an order.

224
00:15:46.237 --> 00:15:48.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barnaby] I don't need lessons on
professionalism from you.

225
00:15:50.116 --> 00:15:51.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you can save the
sympathy.

226
00:15:52.994 --> 00:15:54.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Tiger] Good talk. Good talk.

227
00:15:59.041 --> 00:16:00.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Agnes] <i>Right. Then we'll proceed.</i>

228
00:16:02.044 --> 00:16:03.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everyone's in position.

229
00:16:03.754 --> 00:16:05.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm going to change things up.

230
00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:07.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For this mission,
open all comm channels to the heroes.

231
00:16:08.092 --> 00:16:09.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On it.

232
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:13.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Agnes] The second this commercial ends,
we're on the air.

233
00:16:14.682 --> 00:16:16.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[timer beeping]

234
00:16:17.643 --> 00:16:22.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Bunny. If that NEXT does show up,
are you, uh, you know--

235
00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:26.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gasping]
-What?

236
00:16:29.155 --> 00:16:31.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rock Bison] <i>Hey! What the hell</i>
<i>just happened?</i>

237
00:16:31.324 --> 00:16:33.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Fire Emblem] <i>Is that who I think it is?</i>

238
00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:37.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Tiger] It's him!

239
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:44.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screaming]

240
00:16:46.714 --> 00:16:48.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's egging us on!

241
00:16:50.218 --> 00:16:52.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rock Bison] <i>Where are you going,</i>
<i>Kotetsu?</i>

242
00:16:52.470 --> 00:16:55.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Where do ya think? I'm
going to save people!

243
00:16:58.809 --> 00:16:59.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Tiger] <i>Hey, Bunny!</i>

244
00:17:00.144 --> 00:17:02.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've got the hideout covered!</i>
<i>You go after the NEXT!</i>

245
00:17:03.523 --> 00:17:05.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Fire Emblem] <i>Teach that wannabe</i>
<i>a lesson for me.</i>

246
00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:11.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whoa!

247
00:17:11.948 --> 00:17:14.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll never take us alive,
ya bastard!

248
00:17:14.492 --> 00:17:17.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you, nuts?
We're here to protect you!

249
00:17:18.329 --> 00:17:19.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're back from commercial.

250
00:17:19.956 --> 00:17:22.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do we do about the broadcast?
Should we call it off?

251
00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:24.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Not a chance.
-But ma'am!

252
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:27.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Roll cameras! I want
those ratings.

253
00:17:28.089 --> 00:17:31.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Think about it, heroes trying to
protect the very criminals

254
00:17:31.467 --> 00:17:32.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they were sent to arrest.

255
00:17:33.177 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can't buy drama like that.

256
00:17:50.653 --> 00:17:51.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

257
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:05.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Lunatic] <i>My fellow heroes!</i>

258
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:08.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I do hope you</i>
<i>can hear me.</i>

259
00:18:09.297 --> 00:18:11.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, who was that?

260
00:18:11.215 --> 00:18:13.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ignore him! Just stay on task.

261
00:18:14.302 --> 00:18:18.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] <i>The justice you seek is</i>
<i>nothing more than a hollow fallacy.</i>

262
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:47.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[suit] <i>Good Luck Mode.</i>

263
00:18:51.047 --> 00:18:52.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

264
00:18:56.052 --> 00:18:57.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah!

265
00:18:58.846 --> 00:19:00.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

266
00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:06.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] <i>You call yourselves heroes, but</i>
<i>you can neither save nor punish anyone.</i>

267
00:19:06.312 --> 00:19:11.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Your so-called bravery is all</i>
<i>in vain. Why do you even bother trying?</i>

268
00:19:13.402 --> 00:19:14.945 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on! Uh!

269
00:19:19.867 --> 00:19:25.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] <i>If you want true justice...</i>
<i>only I can give it to you.</i>

270
00:19:30.252 --> 00:19:34.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What a shame. Is the
show already over?

271
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:36.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you part of
Ouroboros?

272
00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:38.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me!

273
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:44.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And if I were, what would you do to me?
Catch me and rip off my suit?

274
00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:47.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tear my body limb from limb?

275
00:19:47.853 --> 00:19:49.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Damn you!

276
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:56.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] Ah, there's the answer
I expected.

277
00:19:57.571 --> 00:20:01.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I understand that the justice you</i>
<i>and your hero pals</i>

